title: Ace in the Hole
overview: A frustrated former big-city journalist now stuck working for an Albuquerque newspaper exploits a story about a man trapped in a cave to rekindle his career, but the situation quickly escalates into an out-of-control circus.

title: Kramer vs. Kramer
overview: Ted Kramer's wife leaves him, allowing for a lost bond to be rediscovered between Ted and his son, Billy. But a heated custody battle ensues over the divorced couple's son, deepening the wounds left by the separation.

title: Requiem for a Dream
overview: The drug-induced utopias of four Coney Island people are shattered when their addictions run deep.

title: Invasion of the Body Snatchers
overview: A small-town doctor learns that the population of his community is being replaced by emotionless alien duplicates.

title: Manchester by the Sea
overview: A depressed uncle is asked to take care of his teenage nephew after the boy's father dies.

title: The Grapes of Wrath
overview: A poor Midwest family is forced off their land. They travel to California, suffering the misfortunes of the homeless in the Great Depression.

title: Beasts of No Nation
overview: A drama based on the experiences of Agu, a child soldier fighting in the civil war of an unnamed African country.

title: Rebel Without a Cause
overview: A rebellious young man with a troubled past comes to a new town, finding friends and enemies.

title: Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans
overview: An allegorical tale about a man fighting the good and evil within him. Both sides are made flesh - one a sophisticated woman he is attracted to and the other his wife.

title: Cat on a Hot Tin Roof
overview: Brick is an alcoholic ex-football player who drinks his days away and resists the affections of his wife. A reunion with his terminal father jogs a host of memories and revelations for both father and son.

title: The Visitor
overview: A college professor travels to New York City to attend a conference and finds a young couple living in his apartment.

title: The Perks of Being a Wallflower
overview: An introvert freshman is taken under the wings of two seniors who welcome him to the real world

title: The Remains of the Day
overview: A butler who sacrificed body and soul to service in the years leading up to World War II realizes too late how misguided his loyalty was to his lordly employer.

title: The Florida Project
overview: Set over one summer, the film follows precocious six-year-old Moonee as she courts mischief and adventure with her ragtag playmates and bonds with her rebellious but caring mother, all while living in the shadows of Walt Disney World.

title: Paths of Glory
overview: After refusing to attack an enemy position, a general accuses the soldiers of cowardice and their commanding officer must defend them.

title: The Verdict
overview: A lawyer sees the chance to salvage his career and self-respect by taking a medical malpractice case to trial rather than settling.

title: The Wrestler
overview: A faded professional wrestler must retire, but finds his quest for a new life outside the ring a dispiriting struggle.

title: One Flew Over the Cuckoo's Nest
overview: A criminal pleads insanity and is admitted to a mental institution, where he rebels against the oppressive nurse and rallies up the scared patients.

title: Miracle in cell NO.7
overview: A story of love between a mentally-ill father who was wrongly accused of murder and his lovely six years old daughter. The prison would be their home. Based on the 2013 Korean movie 7-beon-bang-ui seon-mul (2013).
stars: ['Aras Bulut Iynemli', 'Nisa Sofiya Aksongur', 'Deniz Baysal', 'Celile Toyon Uysal']

title: Bride of Frankenstein
overview: Mary Shelley reveals the main characters of her novel survived: Dr. Frankenstein, goaded by an even madder scientist, builds his monster a mate.
